Felix Fielding (24 February 1858 – 4 February 1910) was an English cricketer. Fielding was a right-handed batsman who fielded as a wicket-keeper. He was born at Lewisham, Kent, and was educated at Malvern College.
Fielding made his first-class debut for Surrey against Oxford University in 1889 at The Oval. He made a further first-class appearance for the county in that season, against Middlesex at The Oval. He also appeared in a first-class match for the South against the North in 1889 at Old Trafford, as well as appearing in the repeat fixture in 1890 at Lord's. In four first-class matches, Fielding scored 100 runs at an average of 20.00, with a high score of 75. This score came for Surrey on debut.He died at Surbiton, Surrey, on 4 February 1910.
